# TradeBot Project Analysis

## 1. Project Introduction

TradeBot is an automated cryptocurrency trading system that enables users to create, manage, and monitor trading bots with various strategies. The application connects to Binance exchange via API to execute trades based on technical indicators like EMA and RSI. It provides comprehensive risk management features including stop-loss, take-profit, trailing stop, daily loss limits, and position sizing controls.

The core goals of TradeBot are to provide a secure, reliable, and user-friendly platform for algorithmic trading with robust risk management, real-time monitoring, and backtesting capabilities. The system is designed for both novice and experienced traders who want to automate their trading strategies while maintaining control over risk parameters.

Target audience includes individual cryptocurrency traders, quantitative analysts, and investors looking to implement systematic trading approaches without developing their own infrastructure from scratch.

## 2. Technical Architecture

The TradeBot application follows a modern microservices architecture with clear separation of concerns between components. The system is built using Python FastAPI for the backend, React for the frontend, and leverages Celery for task scheduling with Redis as the message broker.
